  "body": "### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6917456/34873213-d85a1b48-f79c-11e7-8b15-51f6f35f17cb.png)\r\n\r\nIf `log4(p, s, t1, t2, t3, t4)` defines the  log opcode, memory from p to p + s represents the data section of the log[0-4] instruction. t1-t4 are calls for topics (or indexed).  Since the opcode support that to be any length. Currently the un-indexed \"data\" parameters ( p & s parameters) of a logging operation is limited to 32 bytes in vyper.\r\n\r\nThe following should work after this fix:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nMyLog: __log__({arg1: indexed(bytes <= 3), arg2: bytes <= 64})\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef foo():\r\n    log.MyLog('bar', 'stuuuuff')\r\n```\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nAdd support for it in vyper. Also look at updating pyethereum's `abi.py`  to interpret `bytes[n]` notation on events.\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![](https://i.pinimg.com/736x/5d/4e/cc/5d4ecc2145f7153a09b44759319784fe--big-eyes-cool-eyes.jpg)",
